New file: embassy/examples/mspm0l1306/src/bin/sleep_demo.rs.

Uses the existing generic executor — NO embassy-mspm0::executor required (per q4d.1 resolution (b)). The generic platform-cortex-m executor already issues WFE between awaits, which on Cortex-M0+ enters MSPM0 SLEEP mode by default (SCR.SLEEPDEEP=0).

#[embassy_executor::main]   // no executor= argument
async fn main(_spawner: Spawner) -> ! {
    let p = embassy_mspm0::init(Config::default());
    let mut led = Output::new(p.PA0, Level::Low);
    led.set_inversion(true);
    let button = Input::new(p.PA14, Pull::Up);  // PA14 per mspm0sleep-7oc

    loop {
        led.set_high();
        Timer::after_millis(100).await;
        led.set_low();
        Timer::after_millis(900).await;
        if button.is_low() {
            info!("button pressed");
        }
    }
}

This binary's whole purpose is to (a) exist as a hardware sample and (b) prove the generic executor's WFE path delivers SLEEP-mode current on MSPM0 without any HAL changes. Measurement is its own task (q4d.10).
